{{User:Immanuelle/Ritual ceremonies of the Imperial Palace updated|en}}
'''The''' {{Nihongo|'''{{ill|Saitan-sai|ja|歳旦祭|en|12=draft|12=draft}}'''|歳旦祭|en}} was one of {{ill|8=ja|9=祭日|the minor festivals|en|12=draft|12=draft}} based on {{ill|8=ja|9=皇室祭祀令|the Imperial Household Rites Act|en|12=draft|12=draft}} that was held on {{ill|8=ja|9=祝祭日|national holidays|en|12=draft|12=draft}} before the Pacific War. Today, it is {{ill|Festival|lt=a ritual|en|12=draft|12=draft}} to celebrate the beginning of the New Year, held at {{ill|8=ja|9=宮中三殿|Three Palace Sanctuaries|lt=the three Imperial Palace shrines|en|12=draft|12=draft}} ( {{ill|8=ja|9=賢所|the Kashiko-dokoro|en|12=draft|12=draft}}, the Koreiden, and the Shinto shrine) on January 1st of {{ill|8=ja|9=新暦|the new calendar|en|12=draft|12=draft}} ( {{ill|New Year's Day|en}} ) <ref> 「年中行事事典」p324 1958th year 5月23日初版発行 {{ill|Nishitsunoi Masayoshi|en|12=draft|12=draft}}編 東京堂出版</ref> .
On New Year's Day, {{ill|Emperor of Japan|the Emperor|en|12=draft|12=draft}} performs a four-way bow in the south garden {{ill|8=ja|9=神嘉殿|of the Shinkaden Hall|en|12=draft|12=draft}}, followed by a prayer in the early morning of the same day at 5:30 a.m. in the three palace sanctuaries, presided over by {{ill|8=ja|9=掌典職|the Chief Cleric|en|12=draft|12=draft}}, who recites {{ill|8=ja|9=祝詞|Norito|lt=a prayer|en|12=draft|12=draft}} . At around 5:40 a.m., the Emperor, dressed in {{ill|8=ja|9=黄櫨染御袍|Kourozen-no-gohou|lt=a yellow lacquer-dyed robe|en|12=draft|12=draft}}, bows after the four-way bow, followed by {{ill|Heir apparent|lt=the Crown Prince|en|12=draft|12=draft}}, dressed in {{ill|8=ja|9=黄丹袍|a yellow robe|en|12=draft|12=draft}} {{Citation needed|date=2017th year 8月28日 (月) 05:12 (UTC)|en}}</link> .
At the {{ill|Ise Grand Shrine|en}} and {{ill|Shinto shrine|lt=other shrines|en|12=draft|12=draft}} across the country, the festival is held as a medium-term festival to pray for the prosperity of {{ill|Family tree of Japanese monarchs|lt=the imperial line|en|12=draft|12=draft}}, bountiful harvests, and protection of the people. <ref>神社本庁「神社祭祀規程」昭和27th year 2月2日 規程第11号</ref>
