'''The''' {{Nihongo|'''{{ill|Saitan-sai|ja|歳旦祭|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saitan-sai|qq=}}'''|歳旦祭|en}} was one of {{ill|8=ja|9=祭日|Festival days|lt=Festival days|lt=The minor festivals|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/8=ja|qq=}} based on {{ill|8=ja|9=皇室祭祀令|Imperial Household Rites Act|lt=Imperial Household Rites Act|lt=The Imperial Household Rites Act|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/8=ja|qq=}} that was held on {{ill|8=ja|9=祝祭日|national holidays|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/8=ja|qq=}} before the Pacific War. Today, it is {{ill|Festival|lt=a ritual|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Festival|qq=}} to celebrate the beginning of the New Year, held at {{ill|8=ja|9=宮中三殿|Three Palace Sanctuaries|lt=the three Imperial Palace shrines|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/8=ja|qq=}} ( {{ill|8=ja|9=賢所|Kashiko-dokoro|lt=Kashiko-dokoro|lt=The Kashiko-dokoro|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/8=ja|qq=}}, the Koreiden, and the Shinto shrine) on January 1st of {{ill|8=ja|9=新暦|the new calendar|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/8=ja|qq=}} ( {{ill|New Year's Day|en|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/New Year's Day|qq=}} ) <ref> 「年中行事事典」p324 1958th year 5月23日初版発行 {{ill|Nishitsunoi Masayoshi|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishitsunoi Masayoshi|qq=}}編 東京堂出版</ref> .

On New Year's Day, {{ill|Emperor of Japan|the Emperor|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor of Japan|qq=}} performs a four-way bow in the south garden {{ill|8=ja|9=神嘉殿|of the Shinkaden Hall|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/8=ja|qq=}}, followed by a prayer in the early morning of the same day at 5:30 a.m. in the three palace sanctuaries, presided over by {{ill|8=ja|9=掌典職|the Chief Cleric|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/8=ja|qq=}}, who recites {{ill|8=ja|9=祝詞|Norito|lt=a prayer|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/8=ja|qq=}} . At around 5:40 a.m., the Emperor, dressed in {{ill|8=ja|9=黄櫨染御袍|Kōrozen|lt=Kōrozen|lt=Kourozen-no-gohou|lt=a yellow lacquer-dyed robe|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/8=ja|qq=}}, bows after the four-way bow, followed by {{ill|Heir apparent|lt=the Crown Prince|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heir apparent|qq=}}, dressed in {{ill|8=ja|9=黄丹袍|Ōni robe|lt=Ōni robe|lt=A yellow robe|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/8=ja|qq=}} {{Citation needed|date=2017th year 8月28日 (月) 05:12 (UTC)|en}}</link> .

At the {{ill|Ise Grand Shrine|en|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ise Grand Shrine|qq=}} and {{ill|Shinto shrine|lt=other shrines|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} across the country, the festival is held as a medium-term festival to pray for the prosperity of {{ill|Family tree of Japanese monarchs|lt=the imperial line|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Family tree of Japanese monarchs|qq=}}, bountiful harvests, and protection of the people. <ref>神社本庁「神社祭祀規程」昭和27th year 2月2日 規程第11号</ref>

